# Component Conventions

## Structure Rules
- **Functional components** with **named exports** only — never default exports, never class components
- Use `'use client'` ONLY when the component requires: hooks that use browser APIs, event listeners, Framer Motion animations with `useAnimation`/`useInView`
- Props: define a TypeScript interface inline above the component

## Example Pattern
```tsx
'use client'

import { SomeIcon } from 'lucide-react'

interface CardProps {
  title: string
  description: string
  icon?: React.ReactNode
  className?: string
}

export function Card({ title, description, icon, className = '' }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div className={`glass p-6 ${className}`}>
      {icon && <span className="text-accent-blue mb-3 block">{icon}</span>}
      <h3 className="text-text-primary font-semibold text-lg mb-2">{title}</h3>
      <p className="text-text-secondary text-sm">{description}</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Styling Rules
- Always use Tailwind classes — never `style={{}}` or inline styles
- Use `.glass` for glassmorphism cards
- Use `.gradient-text` for gradient headings
- Use `.section` wrapper for page sections
- Use `.tag` for skill/tech pills
- Use `.btn-gradient` / `.btn-outline` for buttons

## Animation Rules
- Wrap scroll-animated sections in `<ScrollReveal>`
- Use `<GlassCard>` for glass containers
- Framer Motion is client-only — keep Server Components animation-free

## Data Rules
- Resume text/data → always from `lib/constants.ts`
- Icons → always from `lucide-react`
- Images → in `public/images/`, use `<img>` with `alt` text (next/image is unoptimized)
